body:
The JSON file is still a raw product, though. In order to use your story, you should first load it in your game's code. For example, we can write the following to a room's OnCreate code:
ct.room.story = ct.yarn.openStory(myStory);
By default, ct.yarn will look for the 'Start' node. If you want to provide another default title, use ct.yarn.openStory(myStory, 'Specific title');
ct.yarn will read your JSON and structure it in a more useful format. You can now use other methods of ct.yarn to navigate your story, search for its nodes and get dialogue options.

